{"questionId":"32943775","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For extra support, Jamali decides to attach a rope, with length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> , to the tent at a point, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math> , on the edge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AT</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The rope will be fixed to the ground at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math>, such that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the rope, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>PQ</mi></mfenced></math>, is straight</li>\n<li>points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> lie on a straight line</li>\n<li>\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is shown in the diagrams.<br><br></p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/a9203a7974a9eb191fe4ca3c98b52fc5a882f7fb.png\" width=\"629\" height=\"249\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the length of the pole, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>OT</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to use Pythagoras’ theorem<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>94</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>93938</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32943775","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.5a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the length of the pole, OT.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
